reviewText:
Never a big fan of Pat O'Brien, BUT Anne Jeffreys was the epitome of underused actresses of the time,
She was both beautiful and a talented actress (married Robert Sterling - co-starred in TV's "Topper" with Leo G.. Carroll).  Jeffreys is the real star of this intriguing movie.
Though it can hardly be called "Film Noir", it is worth having in your library.
Walter Slezak is a perfectly cast as the "heavy".

Typical old pseudo-film noir.  But I love these old films. I try to collect all the [post war film noir.
The players and setting were watchable..
